is very compelling that

00:31:51.710 --> 00:31:54.010 align:middle line:90%
clearly contradicts his view?

00:31:54.010 --> 00:31:58.510 align:middle line:84%
And van Beek completely refused
to publish Scranton's work

00:31:58.510 --> 00:32:01.020 align:middle line:84%
in his own academic
journal, and Scranton then

00:32:01.020 --> 00:32:03.890 align:middle line:84%
had to go to others
who were also

00:32:03.890 --> 00:32:06.850 align:middle line:84%
academics in the same
field and they were

00:32:06.850 --> 00:32:08.780 align:middle line:90%
able to be more open-minded?

00:32:08.780 --> 00:32:12.750 align:middle line:84%
Yes, it's entirely possible
that somebody like van Beek

00:32:12.750 --> 00:32:16.720 align:middle line:84%
may have been paid to discredit
the work of Laird Scranton.

00:32:16.720 --> 00:32:20.360 align:middle line:84%
There is a force that doesn't
want us to know the truth, that

00:32:20.360 --> 00:32:22.700 align:middle line:84%
doesn't want us to
know what's going on

00:32:22.700 --> 00:32:26.540 align:middle line:84%
and wants to keep the blanket
over this so that we're all

00:32:26.540 --> 00:32:30.390 align:middle line:84%
sleeping in that consensus,
warm blanket of reality that

00:32:30.390 --> 00:32:32.420 align:middle line:90%
says everything's fine.

00:32:32.420 --> 00:32:34.860 align:middle line:84%
And civilization
really began in Sumer

00:32:34.860 --> 00:32:37.700 align:middle line:84%
and it didn't start to get
anywhere until Ancient Greece,

00:32:37.700 --> 00:32:39.310 align:middle line:84%
and it's all had
a nice progression

00:32:39.310 --> 00:32:41.690 align:middle line:84%
from hunter-gatherers
up to the present day.

00:32:41.690 --> 00:32:42.920 align:middle line:90%
It's not true.

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:45.790 align:middle line:84%
Civilization had
attained a high peak,

00:32:45.790 --> 00:32:49.170 align:middle line:84%
